reviewText: It's aiight if you're into the early pageantry contests
I love this Miss Continental Pageant.  I buy the DVD to this pageant every year.
I recieved the dvd, put it in the dvd player and It would not register. I thought is was a blank dvd, to my surprise the dvd was damaged. It had a crack in it. So that was a lost of money.

I bought this dvd.  Although everybody here has a bad comment to say , I dont.  I have followed the Continental pageant circut for many years and its quite entertaining watching these girls enter the pageant for years to win this crown which is by far the most pristigious crown in the states today, everyone who is everyone in the entertainment Industry  started off or have somehow passed through these doors one time in their lives. Continental title holders include, Candice Cayne ( Dirty Sexy Money series star, Starrbooty movie Star ), Mimi Marks( Dennis Rodmans Ex girlfriend and showgirl at the Baton Chicago, appeared in Janet Jacksons videos) Erica Andrews{ title holder maroon 5 video, elbow rubber to the stars) and the list goes on.  This is where it all began for the modern day mainstream transexual entertainers that we see today in the movies , film, TV, and mainstream entertainment.  It is a collectors item.  I only wish Jim Flint ( owner of The Baton Chicago and Miss Continental Pageantry Systems) would sell all the years of continental on Amazon in one big set for us to buy , that would be great.  So for all you negative nancys who don't like the video , its ok return it cause one day you'll regret it
This was not what I thought it was going to be. I had heard that it was entertaining and that was not the case. I could not sit through the whole thing. It was just that bad.
The production of this video is not good because it was recorded back in 1985.  I won't say who won but the pageant was interesting.

The production values are very poor. It is a wonder that it ever made it to tape or DVD. I am transsexual and collect as much trans-related media and books as I can possibly afford, but this was a waste of money. As for the condition of the arrival, it was poor as well. The case was broken. The DVD was intact. Sending it back for replacement was not worth the effort. It was that bad!
